#After Dataset Import

weight.height$Weight <- weight.height$Weight * 0.4536
p <- weight.height$Weight > "90"
weight.height <- weight.height %>% mutate(Diabetic_Patient = p)
a <- (weight.height$Height * 0.3048)/12
weight.height <- weight.height %>% mutate(BMI = weight.height$Weight/(a*a))
b <- weight.height$Gender == "Male" & weight.height$BMI > "25"
c <- weight.height$Gender == "Female" & weight.height$BMI > "28"
k <- b|c
weight.height <- weight.height %>% mutate(BP = ifelse(k,"High_BP",NA))
d <- round(weight.height$Weight)
f <- c("62","74","58","47","81","77","49","53","69","89")
e <- d %in% f
weight.height$BP[c(150:212,640:649,1823:1967,4566:4672,7234:7351,9600:9700)] <- "Low_BP"

#Plot Height vs Weight

n <- weight.height %>% ggplot(aes(Weight,Height)) + geom_point(alpha = 0.2)
n

#Height Graphs for both Gender

g <- weight.height %>% ggplot(aes(Height, fill = Gender)) + geom_density(alpha = 0.2)
g

#Weight Graphs for both Gender

h <- weight.height %>% ggplot(aes(Weight, fill = Gender)) + geom_density(alpha = 0.2)
h

#BMI Graph (BMI = Body Mass Index)

i <- weight.height %>% ggplot(aes(Ratio,BMI, fill = Gender)) + geom_boxplot(aes(x = Weight/Height, y = BMI))
i

#High BP Graph

j <- weight.height %>% filter(BP == "High_BP") %>% ggplot(aes(BP,Weight/Height, col = Gender)) + geom_boxplot()
j

#Low BP Graph

l <- weight.height %>% filter(BP == "Low_BP") %>% ggplot(aes(BP,Weight/Height, col = Gender)) + geom_boxplot()
l

#Probability Density Plot

x <- weight.height$BMI
y <- data.frame(x,f = dnorm(x,mean(x),sd(x))) %>% ggplot(aes(x,f)) + geom_line(col = "red")
y <- y + ggtitle("Probability Density Plot Of BMI") + xlab(("BMI")) + ylab("Probability Density")
y

#Means ans Standard Deviations

m <- weight.height %>% group_by(Gender) %>% summarise(Mean_Heights = mean(Height),SD_Heights = sd(Height),Mean_Weights = mean(Weight), SD_Weights = sd(Weight), Mean_BMI = mean(BMI), SD_BMI = sd(BMI))
m

#Corrrelation

p <- weight.height %>% filter(Gender == "Male") %>% select(BMI)
q <- weight.height %>% filter(Gender == "Male") %>% select(Weight)
mu_x <- mean(weight.height$BMI)
mu_y <- mean(weight.height$Weight)
s_x <- sd(weight.height$BMI)
s_y <- sd(weight.height$Weight)
r <- cor(weight.height$BMI,weight.height$Weight)

#Regression

weight.height %>% ggplot(aes(BMI,Weight)) + geom_point(alpha = 0.4) + geom_abline(slope = 4.84661, intercept = -50.24245) + ggtitle("Regression Given BMI")

weight.height %>% mutate(z_BMI = round((BMI - mean(BMI)) / sd(BMI))) %>% filter(z_BMI %in% -2:2) %>% ggplot() + stat_qq(aes(sample = Weight)) + facet_wrap( ~ z_BMI) + ggtitle("Stratified Weight Given BMI")

#Correlation and Regression vice-versa

m_1 <- r * s_y / s_x 
b_1 <- mu_y - m_1*mu_x
m_2 <- r * s_x / s_y 
b_2 <- mu_x - m_2 * mu_y
weight.height %>% ggplot(aes(BMI, Weight)) + geom_point(alpha = 0.35) + geom_abline(intercept = b_1, slope = m_1, col = "blue") + geom_abline(intercept = -b_2/m_2, slope = 1/m_2, col = "red")
